feat: copy visible persons logic from desktop version

Created visible_persons.js with full copy of desktop version logic:
- collectVisiblePersons() - BFS collection of all related persons
- isAncestor() - check if person is ancestor
- applyCollapse() - apply collapsed_branches flag
- applyFocusMode() - apply focus mode (hide ancestors)
- applyFilters() - apply gender, status, photos_only filters
- getVisiblePersons() - main function combining all steps

Updated tree.js to use getVisiblePersons() instead of custom collect().

This provides identical behavior to desktop version:
- Shows all ancestors, descendants, siblings, spouses
- Respects collapsed_branches flag
- Supports focus mode
- Supports all filters
